  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (W-EP-02 adversarial)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. This synthetic adversarial package embeds W-EP-02: one ValidationResult carries a detailed prose narrative describing the simulation campaign that produced it, but lacks the structured prov:wasGeneratedBy link to the generating Activity. A reviewer may accept the narrative as sufficient provenance, masking the broken structured traceability.",
