    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "The credibility assessment team accepted the model for the stated COU on the basis that all seven assessed credibility factors demonstrated achieved levels within one gradation of required levels, and the Monte Carlo UQ results showed that the 90th-percentile NIH prediction interval satisfied the absolute clinical threshold across all five operating points. The detailed validation narrative for the hemolysis index comparison (VR-002) was accepted as sufficient documentation of the generation process; the absence of a structured activity record was not flagged during review. Six factors remain as epistemic gaps at MRL 5 and are acknowledged as limitations of the current evidence package.",
